; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures AFE and Unity Gain mode.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Supply power to input port by a suitable instrument or make a environment to generate 1V.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. AFE 
;    3. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. AFE0    : PA7 (AO1)
;               : PA6 (AIN1)
;               : PA3 (AIP1)
;
; E. Port Connection
;    1. Supply Power + ----> PA3 (AIP1)
;       PA7(AO1) ----------> PA6 (AIN1)
;
; F. Circuit Configuration
;                                       
;                   -----------------
;                   |               |
;                   |     | \       |
;                   ------|- \      |
;                         |   --------- Vout
;         Vin ------------|+ /
;                         | /
;
;               < Unity Gain Amplifier >
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; AFE1
; 1. Config                    : [ 1 i g ]
;    Operation                 : i (Any operation can be possible.)
;    Mode                      : g (Unity Gain)
;
; PCU (PAx)
; 1. Port Group                : 0 (PCU Port A)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 0 3 a 7 ] [ 0 6 a 7 ] [ 0 7 a 7 ]
;    Pin Number                : 3 / 6 / 7
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 7 (AIP1) / 7 (AIN1) / 7 (AO1)
;

; PCU (PAx)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 3 a 7'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 6 a 7'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 7 a 7'
mpause 30

; AFE0
sendln 'cm afe'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 1 i g'
mpause 30
sendln 'log on 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 1'
